Key Match Events: Estonia lost 0-1 to Slovakia in their UEFA Nations League match on September 5, 2024.
Tomáš Suslov scored the only goal of the match in the 70th minute.
Estonian goalkeeper Karl Jakob Hein made strong saves early in the game.
David Hancko and Ondrej Duda both struck the woodwork for Slovakia.
Ioan Yakovlev's attempt at goal in the 88th minute was cleared by Slovakia captain Milan Škriniar.
Post-Match Reflections: Estonian head coach Jürgen Henn expressed disappointment but praised his team's defensive efforts.
Henn highlighted the need for more decisiveness and directness in the penalty area.
Henn was pleased with the team's adaptation to Slovakia's play style.
Estonian goalkeeper Karl Jakob Hein acknowledged Slovakia's quality and reflected on the team's resilience.
